caption: It always ends in tiers......
I shouldn't be telling you this but I saw her last week on a different cake.
Actually, I'm vanilla. Red Velvet is my stripper name.
I was married once.  Didn’t work out.  She was a tart.
Trust me, it’ll all end in tiers
Bad news. Edith left with the DJ.  I guess you can't have your cake and Edith, too.
Whoa, the cake you fell off of must have been huge!
Your wedding,my funeral.
Just like me, you'll soon be brought down a few levels and consumed by family.
Hey-- you want a piece of me?!
I can keep it together during the ceremony. The reception is where I fall to pieces.
So I says to the genie, ‘Make me a wedding cake.’ Big mistake.
I’m expensive, unhealthy, and I don’t last. So yes, I am a metaphor.
I’m not just a pretty face, I have layers
Psst—the salad says its olive oil is the only virgin at this wedding.
She knows about the cupcake.
So what, she didn’t show. I think we both dodged a bullet here, Ted.
No, I'm not gluten free; a talking cake isn't enough for you?
She may be marrying you, but you’ll never satisfy her like I do.
I know it’s only your birthday, but your mother wanted me to remind you you’re not getting any younger.
I sing, too. Get it? Icing.
You’re seriously marrying a woman who chose carrot cake?
Only one of us is getting out of here in one piece.
Yeah, I thought you’d be taller, too.
How do you know we're not just standing on a bigger cake?
If you run away now you can save both of us.
This marriage is wrong on so many different levels!
I love a wedding, but I always end up shedding a tier or two.
You probably get this a lot but you look a lot like the groom, only bigger
What are you looking at pal?  At least you get to leave here in one piece!
